\section{What this catches}{

Aberrant, inconsistent response patterns -- random and patterned responding --
that scale poorly against the sample's item ordering. Unlike most indirect
indices it \strong{abstains on} rather than misses pure straightlining (a
zero-variance row is unscalable); pair it with \code{\link[=cier_longstring]{cier_longstring()}} and
\code{\link[=cier_irv]{cier_irv()}}, which target the straightlining it cannot score.
}

